Manage the current feature's pull request:

Arguments: $ARGUMENTS (create|update|status|merge)

Requires GitHub MCP to be configured.

## Actions:

### create
Create a new PR from current branch to main/master:
1. Identify current feature from branch name or feature-list.json
2. Create PR with:
   - Title: Feature name
   - Body: Description + verification checklist + "Closes #XX"
3. Update feature-list.json with prNumber
4. Report PR URL

### update
Update existing PR with latest progress:
1. Find PR number from feature-list.json
2. Update PR body with:
   - Current progress from claude-progress.json
   - Updated verification status
3. Add comment summarizing changes

### status
Check PR status:
1. Find PR number from feature-list.json
2. Report:
   - PR state (open/closed/merged)
   - Review status (approved/changes requested/pending)
   - CI/CD check status
   - Merge conflicts if any

### merge
Merge the PR if ready:
1. Check PR is approved
2. Check CI passes
3. Check no merge conflicts
4. Merge PR (squash or merge based on repo settings)
5. Delete feature branch
6. Mark feature as passes: true in feature-list.json
7. Update claude-progress.json
